HEADWORD: Clinographic
<hw>Cli"no*graph"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kli`nein</grk> to incline + <ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Pertaining to that mode of projection in drawing in which the rays
of light are supposed to fall obliquely on the plane of
projection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clinoid</ent>⟦br⟧
